Sec. 146.001. BILL OF SALE OR TRANSFER REQUIRED. (a) If a
person in this state sells or transfers a horse, mule, jack, jennet,
ox, or head of cattle, the actual delivery of the animal must be
accompanied by a written transfer to the purchaser from the vendor.
The written transfer must give the marks and brands of the animal
and, if more than one animal is transferred, must give the number
transferred.
(b) On the trial of the right of property in an animal sold or
